com.example.myurbanflix

Class FirestoreHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.myurbanflix.FirestoreHelper

  • public class FirestoreHelper
extends java.lang.Object
    Used to access the firestore database from one central location. Gives clients Queries from database matching particular search parameters they desire, and appropriately logs in users for the client (or keeps them logged out if they have invalid credentials).

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      FirestoreHelper()
      Initialize the db helper's connection to the firestore (where our database is hosted).

      • FirestoreHelper

        public FirestoreHelper()
        Initialize the db helper's connection to the firestore (where our database is hosted). This constructor is only called once, in main activity, to initialize a single public static instance of the FirestoreHelper that other classes can use freely

      • logInUser

        public void logInUser(com.google.android.gms.tasks.OnCompleteListener<com.google.firebase.firestore.QuerySnapshot> loginInIfLegal,
                      java.lang.String un_or_pw,
                      java.lang.String password)
        Performs the actions dictated by a listener when a query to the database is complete. The query searches the database for a user with matching username or email and password. If the query is non-empty (the user exists), the on complete listener will log them in, otherwise, it will display a warning to the user
        Parameters:
        loginInIfLegal - - the listener that will be called when this query is complete
        un_or_pw - - the input username or email from the text field in login
        password - - the password from the text field in login
